These are instructions for installing Biblios as a standalone web application.

Dependencies:
Apache2 with proxy_http module
Perl
Perl modules:
	CGI, CGI::Carp, MARC::Record, MARC::File::XML, File::Temp, File::BaseName, JSON, Term::Clui, Template, File::Slurp
Pazpar2
Google Gears plugin for your web browser (Internet Explorer 6/7 or FireFox), available here: http://gears.google.com/.

1.Get a copy of biblios, via git 

	git clone git://git.biblios.net/pub/scm/biblios.git

or by downloading a prepackaged .tar.gz or .zip file:

	wget http://biblios.net/sites/default/files/biblios-0.9.tar.gz
	tar xzvf biblios.tar.gz

OR

	wget http://biblios.net/sites/default/files/biblios-0.9.zip
	unzip biblios.zip

2.Go to your unpacked biblios tree
 
	cd biblios

3. Generate packed and debug versions of biblios files

	make 

4. Enable apache2's proxy_http module:

	sudo /usr/sbin/a2enmod proxy_http
	sudo /usr/sbin/apache2ctl force-reload

5. Add reverse proxies to your apache configuration file.  Substitute your own server urls where indicated in the configuration section which follows:
<IfModule mod_proxy.c>
       ProxyRequests Off

       <Proxy *>
        AddDefaultCharset off
        Order deny,allow
        Allow from all
       </Proxy>

       ProxyVia Off

       # proxy for pazpar2 daemon (required to search z39.50 databases)
       ProxyPass /pazpar2/search.pz2 http://localhost:9004/search.pz2

       # proxy for sru authority server (required for authority-controlled fiels dropdowns to work)
       #ProxyPass /kohaauth/ <your koha sru auth server e.g. http://eowyn.metavore.com:9999/>
   
</IfModule>

6. Edit the conf/biblios-dist.conf file to include any static Z39.50 search targets or remote ils (koha) targets.  Follow the comments in the biblios-dist.conf file for the syntax.  

7. Rename the biblios-dist.conf file to biblios.conf.

8. Download and install PazPar2, available here: http://www.indexdata.dk/pazpar2/.

9. Run pazpar2 with included config files and search targets with the following command from your biblios directory.
 
	pazpar2 -D -l logs/pazpar2.log -f conf/pazpar2/pazpar2.cfg -t conf/pazpar2/biblios-pazpar2.cfg

10. Install biblios and cgi scripts into appropriate paths for your web server using the included install.pl script.  You will be prompted for the location of your webserver's htdocs directory and cgi-bin directory:

./install.pl

11. Point your browser to the appropriate path and catalog away...
